Subject: Re: [T2] FAST idle  -  the (partial) answer to broken throttle

On Sat, 17 Jul 2010, Robert Mann wrote:

> 	My elation at passing the half-yearly Warrant of Fitness test was 
> soon deflated by finding I had no throttle control just as I tried to merge 
> onto the main hwy at the bottom of the Silverdale gulch.  The linkage just 
> under the accelerator pedal was OK; deduction (confirmed by pulling the inner 
> free) broken cable.

in a similar situation but much much further away from home and in the 
mountains.  I ran a wire from the throttle linkage in the engine 
compartment thru a opening into the body and to the front, hand throttle 
by pulling on wire...... got home with very little delay.

carry spare cable
or at least vice grips and wire


Bob
